Company Overview of Ecochlor, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Ecochlor, Inc. develops and commercializes ballast water treatment solutions for ship builders and ship owners worldwide. It offers ballast water treatment system, a two-step process that includes filtration and treatment with ClO2; eliminates aquatic species, bacteria, and other pathogens from ballast water with ClO2 technology; and is effective on various aquatic invasive species, including zooplankton, phytoplankton, algae, microorganisms, pathogens, and viruses. The company also provides seawater filtration systems. Its products are installed on large bulkers and tankers. In addition, it offers marine engineering, naval architecture, chemical treatment, shipboard installation, and techni...
Ecochlor, Inc. develops and commercializes ballast water treatment solutions for ship builders and ship owners worldwide. It offers ballast water treatment system, a two-step process that includes filtration and treatment with ClO2; eliminates aquatic species, bacteria, and other pathogens from ballast water with ClO2 technology; and is effective on various aquatic invasive species, including zooplankton, phytoplankton, algae, microorganisms, pathogens, and viruses. The company also provides seawater filtration systems. Its products are installed on large bulkers and tankers. In addition, it offers marine engineering, naval architecture, chemical treatment, shipboard installation, and technical and regulatory certification support services. The company was founded in 2001 and is based in Maynard, Massachusetts. It has manufacturing facilities in North Haven, Connecticut; and Shanghai, China.
Detailed Description


