Ecochlor, Inc. Key Developments

Ecochlor, Inc. Signs Agreement with Minerva Marine, Inc. for the Potential Supply of BWT Systems
Apr 17 17
Ecochlor, Inc. announced that it has signed an agreement with Minerva Marine, Inc. for the potential supply of BWT Systems for up to 30 vessels under its management for installations in accordance to the IMO and USCG implementation plan. The Ecochlor technology was selected for retrofit in Minerva's managed bulkers and tankers varying in size from MRs to VLCCs.


Ecochlor, Inc. Appoints Chip Herzog as Chief Financial Officer
Jan 9 17
Ecochlor, Inc. announced that Chip Herzog has joined the company’s leadership team as chief financial officer. Mr. Herzog, a seasoned financial executive, brings with him 30 years of business experience in financial and operations management, and accounting. As a financial professional, he has focused on partnering with operating executives, utilizing core financial and operational data to generate insight and guide decision-making. Prior to joining the company, Herzog worked at Otis Elevator Company, Boston Scientific, Pratt & Whitney and Spirit AeroSystems.


Ecochlor, Inc. Announces Completion of Three Retrofit Installations for SCF Novoship Technical Management
Sep 13 16
Ecochlor, Inc. announced the completion of three retrofit installations for SCF Novoship Technical Management. The Ecochlor Technical Services Team, along with engineering firm Argo Navis Marine Consulting & Engineering Ltd., were onsite at dry dock in Croatia to install the ballast water treatment system (BWTS) on the NS Stream, and at dry dock in Turkey to complete installation on two sister ships, the NS Consul and NS Century.


